SIMPLE: semen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semen
<hw>Se"men</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"m⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Semina</plw>
<pr>(s⟦ecr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*n⟦adot⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., from the root of
<ets>serere</ets>, <ets>satum</ets>, to sow. See <er>Sow</er> to scatter
seed.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The seed of
plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The seed or fecundating fluid
of male animals; sperm. It is a white or whitish viscid fluid secreted
by the testes, characterized by the presence of spermatozoids to which
it owes its generative power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Semen contra</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Semen
cinae</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>Semen cynae</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a
strong aromatic, bitter drug, imported from <city>Aleppo</city> and
Barbary, said to consist of the leaves, peduncles, and unexpanded
flowers of various species of <gen>Artemisia</gen>;
wormseed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semeniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
